    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe documentation states the the valid values for `scrollback` are `1 - 100000`.\r\n\r\nThere is also the value of `-1` which appears to default to the max `100000` here\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/lua/vim/_meta/options.lua#L5115\r\n\r\nI was looking at https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/terminal.c#L245 and think that\r\n```c\r\n  buf->b_p_scbk =          // 'scrollback' (initialize local from global)\r\n                  (p_scbk < 0) ? 10000 : MAX(1, p_scbk);\r\n```\r\nmay be incorrect. Other places in the code are referencing, `#define SB_MAX 100000  // Maximum 'scrollback' value.`. \r\n\r\nIf is set `scrollback` = `-1` it is setting the default value `10000` and not the max `100000`.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe global (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/test/functional/terminal/scrollback_spec.lua#L513) and local (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/test/functional/terminal/scrollback_spec.lua#L518) values of `-1` also have different values. \r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean --noplugin -n +'set scrollback=-1' +'set number' +'lua vim.fn.termopen([[hexdump -e \"\\\"%u\\\"\" /dev/urandom | fold -w 10 | head -200000]])'\r\n\r\n# 10053 lines\r\n```\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean --noplugin -n +'set scrollback=100000' +'set number' +'lua vim.fn.termopen([[hexdump -e \"\\\"%u\\\"\" /dev/urandom | fold -w 10 | head -200000]])'\r\n\r\n# 100053 lines\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nðŸ¤· I'm not sure. I am assuming `-1` should represent the max.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1104+g9fc321c97\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
